msgid "Example of a locality *b* as offsets *x* and *y* in orthogonal directions (from the corrected center *a* of a feature (i.e. stock watering point). The coordinates *b* (8 km E and 6 km N of *a* are surrounded by a bounding box 1 km square *c* showing the uncertainty due to distance precision of 1 km. The net uncertainty from distance precision is represented by a circle *d* that circumscribes the bounding box and which has a radial of 0.707 km. By convention the headings for localities with offsets in orthogonal directions are exactly in the specified directions and contribute no uncertainty due to direction precision."
